P_0(x_0,y_0,z_0)
z^2=a(x^2+y^2)
P_0
 z^2 = a \left( x^2+y^2 \right ) \\ \left \{ \begin{array}{ccc} 2z z_x &=& 2ax \\ 2zz_y &=& 2a y \end{array} \right . \implies \left \{ \begin{array}{ccc} z_x &=& \frac {ax}z \\ z_y &=& \frac{a y}z \end{array} \right . 
 z-z_0 = \frac a{z_0} \left[ x_0(x-x_0) + y_0(y-y_0) \right ] 
 z_0 z = a \left( x_0 x + y_0 y\right ) 
a
n = (ax_0, ay_0, -z_0)
 \frac {x-x_0}{ax_0} = \frac {y-y_0}{ay_0} = -\frac {z-z_0}{z_0} 
